<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,258,499]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,330,355]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName box="[793,868,331,354]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parcus">
<emphasis box="[793,868,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">parcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: acrostichals absent; median volsella wartlike; and inferior volsella without basal projection, with thin subapical setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
